Nanofiber scaffolds have been exposed to an open round container with a diameter of 1.2 cm for the purpose of calculating the amount of Water vapor transmission rate. In the following, we have filled the container with 5 ml of sterilized water, which is about one quarter of the container's height, and had the vessel placed in an oven at 35 °C with the humidity of 35% for 24 h. Lastly, the WVTR has been calculated by the usage of the following Eq.12,92.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
