				\begin{document}$$WVTR=\frac{\Delta W}{A}$$\end{document}WVTR=ΔWAwhere ΔW represents the change of water weight (g) and A is the open surface area of the container (1.13 × 10–4 m2). A round container without nanofiber scaffolds has been considered as a control group. The amount of WVTR has been calculated for three times in regards to each sample and the results had been reported as mean ± standard deviation.
